OL,3,CJersey braced for hottest day of the
OL,4,Cyear so far as safety guidance issued
OL,6,FThe advice offers several steps
OL,7,Fpeople, can take to avoid heat
OL,8,Fexhaustion, dehydration and
OL,9,Fheatstroke.JIt says:J Avoid going
OL,10,Foutside during the hottest time of day
OL,11,F11am to 3pm
OL,13,F Leave strenuous activities for later
OL,14,Fon in the day when it is cooler
OL,16,F Take cold baths and showers
OL,18,F Drink plenty of water and avoid
OL,19,Fcoffee and alcohol
